<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="42" type="discussion">
<paragraph pageId="9" pageNumber="42">Discussion.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="9" pageNumber="42">
The sample used (Wood 10428) in the molecular study by 
<bibRefCitation author="Clark, JR" journalOrPublisher="Molec. Phylogen. Evol." pageId="24" pageNumber="57" pagination="982 - 994" publicationUrl="10.1016/j.ympev.2009.09.002" refId="B6" refString="Clark, JR, Wagner, WL, Roalson, EH, 2009. Patterns of diversification and ancestral range reconstruction in the Southeast Asian-Pacific angiosperm lineage Cyrtandra (Gesneriaceae). Molec. Phylogen. Evol. 53: 982 - 994, 10.1016/j.ympev.2009.09.002" title="Patterns of diversification and ancestral range reconstruction in the Southeast Asian-Pacific angiosperm lineage Cyrtandra (Gesneriaceae)." url="10.1016/j.ympev.2009.09.002" volume="53" year="2009">Clark et al. (2009)</bibRefCitation>
was identified as 
<taxonomicName class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Gesneriaceae" genus="Cyrtandra" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Tubiflorae" pageId="9" pageNumber="42" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="nukuhivensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="42">Cyrtandra nukuhivensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but during this taxonomic revision it was re-identified as the closely related 
<taxonomicName class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Gesneriaceae" genus="Cyrtandra" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Tubiflorae" pageId="9" pageNumber="42" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="thilbaultii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="42">Cyrtandra thilbaultii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
